{{Lunisolar September}} '''September 30''' is the 30th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|12=draft|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|12=draft|12=draft}} .
As with all other days 30 of the Sino-Japanese calendar it sometimes happens and sometimes does not depending on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref>Months are also annotated as either long ({{zh|c=大|l=big}} for months with 30 days) or short ({{zh|c=小|l=small}} for months with 29 days). There are also other elements of the traditional Chinese calendar.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
== Events ==
* {{ill|Kanpyō|ja|寛平|1=Kanpyō (era)|lt=Kanpyō|qq= (era)|12=draft|12=draft}} 6 ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|894|ja|894th year|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 1|ja|11月1日|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The abolition of the {{ill|Kentōshi|ja|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)|12=draft|12=draft}} (Japanese missions to Tang China) is decided based on the recommendation of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|12=draft|12=draft}} .
* {{ill|Genroku|ja|Genroku|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1688|ja|1688th year|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 23|ja|10月23日|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The era name changes from {{ill|Jōkyō (Japan)|ja|貞享|12=draft|12=draft}} to Genroku.
== Births ==
* {{ill|Chenghua|ja|成化|12=draft|12=draft}} 8 (Julian {{ill|1472|ja|1472nd year|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 31|ja|10月31日|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Wang Yangming|ja|王陽明|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|Ming dynasty|ja|明|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Confucian scholar|ja|1=Ru (Confucian scholar)|儒学者|zh|儒生|12=draft|12=draft}} and founder of {{ill|Yangmingism|ja|陽明学|12=draft|12=draft}} .
* {{ill|1917|ja|1917th year|12=draft|12=draft}} – {{ill|Park Chung-hee|ja|朴正煕|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|military officer|ja|Military Personnel|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|politician|ja|政治家|12=draft|12=draft}} , and President of South Korea (+ {{ill|1979|ja|1979th year|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths ==
