As with all other days 30 of the Sino-Japanese calendar it sometimes happens and sometimes does not depending on the lunar cycle.<ref>https://www.ndl.go.jp/koyomi/e/history/index.html</ref>Months are also annotated as either long ({{zh|c=大|l=big}} for months with 30 days) or short ({{zh|c=小|l=small}} for months with 29 days). There are also other elements of the traditional Chinese calendar.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref>
== Events ==
* {{ill|Kanpyō|ja|寛平|1=Kanpyō (era)|lt=Kanpyō|qq= (era)|1=Kanpyō (era)|lt=Kanpyō|qq= (era)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 6 ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|894|ja|894th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|November 1|ja|11月1日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – The abolition of the {{ill|Kentōshi|ja|Kentōshi (envoy to Tang China)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Japanese missions to Tang China) is decided based on the recommendation of {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|qq=draft}} .
* {{ill|Genroku|ja|Genroku|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|1688|ja|1688th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 23|ja|10月23日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – The era name changes from {{ill|Jōkyō (Japan)|ja|貞享|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to Genroku.
== Births ==
* {{ill|Chenghua|ja|成化|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 8 (Julian {{ill|1472|ja|1472nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 31|ja|10月31日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Wang Yangming|ja|王陽明|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , {{ill|Ming dynasty|ja|明|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Confucian scholar|ja|1=Ru (Confucian scholar)|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and founder of {{ill|Yangmingism|ja|陽明学|qq=draft|qq=draft}} .
* {{ill|1917|ja|1917th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Park Chung-hee|ja|朴正煕|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , {{ill|military officer|ja|Military Personnel|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , {{ill|politician|ja|政治家|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , and President of South Korea (+ {{ill|1979|ja|1979th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ).
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Kan'ō (Japan)|ja|Kan'ō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 2 / {{ill|Shōhei (Japan)|ja|正平|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 6 (Julian {{ill|1351|ja|1351st year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 20|ja|10月20日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Musō Soseki|ja|夢窓疎石|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , a monk of the {{ill|Rinzai school|ja|臨済宗|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (* {{ill|1275|ja|1275th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 8 (Gregorian {{ill|1796|ja|1796年|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Makino Sadachika|ja|牧野貞長|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , {{ill|politician|ja|政治家|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (* {{ill|1733|ja|1733rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ).
